caption: A lovely green space located in the 11th, with plenty of seating, to enjoy a rest. During our visit to Paris we have enjoyed exploring the many gardens, parks and green spaces within this amazing city, this one adds to the beauty of the area.

What a beautiful place to just sit down and take the beauty of the neighborhood and this fantastic city. Peaceful and triangle! And the church/cathedral Saint-Ambroise, Paris at the end of this park/green space is the cherry on top.
Very nice park with some additional features like free Paris drinking water. Nice church there also.
One of my favorite spots to walk when cutting through the neighborhood. The views of the church are spectacular. The gardens are charming. Worth the walk.

I just love this park and this neighborhood as a whole. Close to Boulangerie Land & Monkeys & Restaurant Aujourd'hui Demain and many more nice places! Often the sun shines brilliantly on the Eglise. Love that as well üòÄ ‚Ä¶

I am impressed by the work the city put into this park, with the gardens, sand areas, the trees, the play apparatus, and the trees. The downside -and it's very detrimental!!- is the trash. UGH!! Inside the fenced area for the smaller children there are cigarette butts EVERYWHERE as well as so much trash that is a choking hazard for little ones. If it is at all possible, please could someone put an equal effort into the maintenance of this park that would honour the work that went into its design.
What a delightful park! You can get sparkling water, on tap, for free! That is something that really adds to my Paris enjoyment.
Gree Park. Some drunk people. But so far ok.

Super place for the kids and parents with many spots to keep them active :-)

Rather modern garden with trees, it is well laid out and planted with trees with play areas for children. This garden of more than 5,000 m2 is designed as a breath of fresh air in this very dense neighborhood: its central axis creates a shortcut between the promenade on Boulevard Richard-Lenoir and Boulevard Voltaire, and opens up a clear view of the Saint-Ambroise church and his square. On the Richard-Lenoir side, the entrance to the perspective offers an abundant setting around a wetland. Opposite the cr√®che, two play areas are set up around a fun meadow where logs from trees cut down in Paris are reused. The heart of the garden, next to Impasse Truillot, is open to artistic expressions: a square hosts cultural events. at the foot of a frescoed wall. On the plot bordering Boulevard Voltaire, a vast lawn is bordered by flowering fallows, vines and fruit trees. A shared garden and an educational garden are accessible to residents and schools in the neighborhood.

Pleasant garden (created in 2018) in the 11th, which allows you to cross from Boulevard Voltaire to Boulevard Richard Lenoir. Large space of 5,000 m2 with its large lawn. Play area for children and fountain, which is very nice in summer! Beautiful view of the Saint Ambroise church and its flowerbed. I recommend this island of greenery

Incredible place not only to go for a walk but also today it is a place of culture! We had the chance today to be present at an excellent cultural event! For ‚Äúeleven moves‚Äù and it was really great!

The long-awaited garden is a breath of fresh air in the neighborhood. Quite far from the boulevards it remains calm. Games for children of all ages have been installed and numerous plants and flowers embellish the park. It's a shame that smokers still haven't understood that they should smoke elsewhere and not throw their butts where the children play.

It's a pure discovery when leaving the Richard Lenoir metro station, lots of well-thought-out motor skills courses with letters and numbers, several plants and flowers! Wooden furniture that fits well, quality water point, selective sorting bin

Pretty renovated and well maintained garden. Clean and quiet, I recommend for a break!

The new park just opened last year. I finally took a walk here today while there was still some sunshine. What is very different is that there are many more play areas for children and fake turf, but it looks very clean and easy to maintain.

Edit 2021: The eastern half of the square was demolished, leveled and rebuilt. It's nice to know that we are rich enough to afford the biennial reconstruction of the squares in Paris. Hopefully the new drainage will work. Still no sports ground for the little ones, I imagine that the collective of neighbors can't stand the noise. Paris is a party... except after 50 years.  ...... 2019: One point because we ended up opening this square, and we needed one. +1 because it is open 24 hours a day - could there be a cultural revolution in the parks and gardens of Paris? On the other hand, in what way is the locked vegetable garden reserved for a privileged few more socially useful than the basketball and football field which, even temporarily, allowed children to play something other than video games? One year later we can say that this garden is working! Just look at the number of people who go there to get some fresh air. Some lawns did not resist, but the break-in is going well. Bravo to the town planners and the Town Hall!

Very beautiful garden, with many flowering plants, vines, aromatic plants. There are also fruit trees, apple trees, fig trees. We were able to chat with the gardeners. There is a wasteland so that the bees can gather nectar.
A very nice layout of the Paris town hall to spend pleasant and friendly moments. Play area for children and lawn set up for picnics. Ideal place for families and meetings with friends.
